    <div class="container">
        <div class="title">Lost Bag Poem</div>
        <div class="poem">
The train exhales me and

a huff of bodies spill out the doors.

I climb the stairs in twos,
reach for my bag
but grasp only air.

Shit!

Lost bag.

I run, but the train outruns me.
So I stop.

I am a child again.
A stupid girl who loses things.

Supervised, supervised—
I must be supervised.
Tie a string around my wrist,
yank me back.

Go away! Go away!
I say to the normal adult who comes near.
You mustn’t love me.

I lose things and miss things,
and I’m embarrassed because
I’m not a real person yet.

And in this fantasy they don’t move at all.
They only stand and look at me plainly and say,
C’mon. Let’s find that bag.
        </div>
